{"type":"text","timestamp":1775862695624,"sessionID":"ses_286582029ffeCTIM14Th9MvEPk","part":{"id":"prt_d79aa1b00001FHuWGj33psREJW","messageID":"msg_d79a9eeab00158q5eR3lDpddHG","sessionID":"ses_286582029ffeCTIM14Th9MvEPk","type":"text","text":"## Verification Report: AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器\n\n### ✅ AR-018 Implementation Status: **COMPLETE & VERIFIED**\n\n| Component | Status | Details |\n|-----------|--------|---------|\n| Tests | ✅ PASSING | 17 tests, 83.6% coverage |\n| Build | ✅ SUCCESS | Binary builds without errors |\n| Constants | ✅ VERIFIED | All 3 constants correctly defined |\n| Reconciler | ✅ VERIFIED | Matches design specification |\n| Error Handling | ✅ VERIFIED | Proper error wrapping and handling |\n\n### ⚠️ Spec Mismatch Detected\n\n**Issue:** The provided spec (`deployment/client-go.md`) describes client-go library generation for API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, but AR-018 uses `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1.Sandbox`.\n\n**API Groups Used:**\n- **AR-018 (agentd)**: `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1.Sandbox` (from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox`)\n- **Spec describes**: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n\nThese are **completely different components** - the agentd controller does not require the client-go library.\n\n### 📊 Client-go Library Status\n\n| Item | Status | Notes |\n|------|--------|-------|\n| client-go directory | ❌ MISSING | No directory exists |\n| Code generation scripts | ❌ MISSING | No `hack/update-codegen.sh` |\n| Makefile | ❌ MISSING | No gen-client target |\n| Runtime API types | ✅ EXISTS | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` |\n| Runtime API tests | ✅ PASSING | All tests passing |\n| Codebase imports | ❌ NONE | No imports of `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` |\n\n### ✅ AR-018 Verification Details\n\n**Constants Verified (`pkg/agentd/constants.go`):**\n- ✅ `SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n- ✅ `LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"last-activity-time\"`\n- ✅ `DefaultRequeueInterval = 30 * time.Second`\n\n**Reconciler Verified (`pkg/agentd/controller.go`):**\n- ✅ Embeds `client.Client` and has `Scheme *runtime.Scheme`\n- ✅ Properly handles NotFound errors\n- ✅ Reads and validates `last-activity-time` annotation\n- ✅ Parses RFC3339 time format with error handling\n- ✅ Calculates expiration time correctly (15-minute timeout)\n- ✅ Deletes expired sandboxes with idempotent logic\n- ✅ Uses `RequeueAfter` for precise scheduling\n- ✅ Proper logging with klog\n\n**Test Coverage: 83.6%** (exceeds 80% requirement)\n\n### 📝 Conclusion\n\n**AR-018 is fully implemented and verified.** All requirements from its design specification are met:\n- ✅ Passive monitoring via Informer\n- ✅ Precise timeout scheduling (15 minutes)\n- ✅ Idempotent operations\n- ✅ Minimal interference with running sandboxes\n- ✅ Annotation-driven communication\n\n**The client-go spec appears to be for a different component** (possibly workload-manager or other components that need to interact with AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter resources). If client-go generation is required, it should be generated as a separate task, not as part of AR-018 verification.","time":{"start":1775862695622,"end":1775862695622}}}
